==Contention 2: Domestic Dependent Nations==


====The status of Indian Tribes as domestic dependent nations codifies the dual character of the American subject: one that is colonialist through the continuing legacy of manifest destiny and one that is anti-colonialist as a product of revolution.  Much like tribes within American borders, the abject Native must remain repressed within the psyche to maintain the coherence of the subject~’s identity.====
